The distribution of tree types in the Welbeck Estate runs as follows;
HARDWOODS 60% (Oak,Sweet Chestnut+Beech) SOFTWOODS 40% (Conifers,mainly Pine)
Parts of the woodland are kept intact for game to breed.Occasionally the tree felling season is interrupted by the game shooting season. The felled timber is used mainly on the estate itself for repair work and for the construction of fencing posts and gates. Between twelve and twenty acres of woodland are farmed annually.The estate also has its own treatment plant which preserves the timber.
